; M3 gate: slur / legato via the `X ~ Y` connector. Same pitch → TIE (extend);
; different pitch → legato NOTE_ON (frequency moves, the note is not re-keyed).
; Covers FM legato chains, a same-pitch tie, a legato into a rest (key-off), and
; PSG legato (frequency moves, attenuation held).
(fm1 :tempo 120 :alg 4 :fb 3 :ar1 31 :tl1 20 :ar4 31 :tl4 8 :len 4
  c ~ d ~ e     ; legato chain: one attack, gliding through d and e
  g ~ g         ; same pitch → tie (extend)
  c ~ e _       ; legato then rest (key-off releases)
  a)
(sqr1 :len 4
  c ~ e ~ g     ; PSG legato: frequency moves, tone stays sounding
  e ~ e
  c _)
